The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as entailment, relation extraction, and question answering, which are typically categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces a new unsupervised method for hypernym detection, which involves vector embeddings and negative sampling, indicating a possible connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its method on multiple datasets, suggesting a possible connection to information retrieval (cs.IR) and data structures (cs.DS).
